From sera Serdar Argic Subject Method employed by the Armenians in 'Genocide of the Muslim People' Source Men Are Like That by Leonard Ramsden The Bobbs Merrill Company Indianapolis pages Memoirs of an Armenian officer who participated in the genocide of million Muslim people first paragraph In this movement we took with us three thousand Turkish soldiers who had been captured by the Russians and left on our hands when the Russians abandoned the During our retreat to Karaklis two thousand of these poor devils were cruelly put to I was sickened by the brutality displayed but could not make any effective Some mercifully were Many of them were burned to The method employed was to put a quantity of straw into a hut and then after crowding the hut with Turks set fire to the Serdar Argic 'We closed the roads and mountain passes that might serve as ways of escape for the Turks and then proceeded in the work of ' Ohanus Appressian 'In Soviet Armenia today there no longer exists a single Turkish ' Sahak Melkonian